# UI Design Rules for DevTools Panel

## CSS Framework & Typography
```css
/* Use system font stack for consistent DevTools integration */
body { 
  font-family: ui-sans-serif, system-ui;
  padding: 10px;
}

/* Monospace for CSV preview readability */
textarea { 
  font-family: monospace;
}
```

## Layout Patterns
```css
/* Row-based layout for form sections */
.row { 
  margin: 8px 0;
}

/* Full-width controls with specific sizing */
textarea { 
  width: 100%; 
  height: 120px;
}

/* Button spacing */
button {
  margin-right: 8px;
}
```

## Component Design Principles
1. **Compact Layout**: DevTools panels have limited space - use efficient layouts
2. **Clear Actions**: Button groups with consistent spacing and visual hierarchy
3. **Immediate Feedback**: Show collection status and data count in real-time
4. **Data Preview**: Always provide textarea preview of collected data

## Form Control Standards
Based on [panel.html](mdc:net2sheet/panel.html) implementation:

```html
<!-- Label-input association with inline styling -->
<label>GAS WebApp URL: <input id="gasUrl" style="width: 60%" /></label>
<button id="save">保存</button>

<!-- Button groups with consistent Japanese labels -->
<button id="start">収集開始</button>
<button id="stop">収集停止</button>
<button id="exportCsv">CSVダウンロード</button>
<button id="send">スプレッドシートへ送信</button>

<!-- Status display with real-time updates -->
<strong>収集件数:</strong> <span id="count">0</span>

<!-- Data preview with helpful placeholder -->
<textarea id="preview" placeholder="ファイル名,URL のプレビュー"></textarea>
```

## Color & Visual Design
- Use minimal colors to match DevTools aesthetic
- Rely on typography hierarchy rather than color for importance
- Ensure sufficient contrast for accessibility
- Use native button and form control styling for consistency

## Responsive Behavior
```css
/* Textarea sizing for data preview */
textarea { 
  height: 120px; 
  resize: vertical; 
  font-family: monospace; /* Better for CSV preview */
}

/* Button spacing for touch-friendly interaction */
button { 
  margin-right: 8px; 
  padding: 4px 8px;
  min-height: 24px;
}
```

## Japanese UI Text Guidelines
- Use clear, concise Japanese for user actions
- Maintain consistency: 収集開始/停止, CSVダウンロード, etc.
- Provide helpful placeholder text in form controls
- Error messages should be informative and in Japanese

## Accessibility Considerations
- Use semantic HTML elements (`<label>`, `<button>`, `<textarea>`)
- Ensure keyboard navigation works properly
- Provide clear visual focus indicators
- Use descriptive text for screen readers

## DevTools Integration
- Keep visual design minimal to blend with DevTools
- Use standard spacing and sizing conventions
- Avoid custom icons unless necessary (stick to text labels)
- Ensure panel works in both light and dark DevTools themes
